What you need to know:

In traditional African medicine, different parts of the tree – bark, roots, leaves and pods – are used to treat various conditions.According to the publication Plant Resources of Tropical Africa, the pounded bark and roots are added to baths to treat skin diseases such as scabies and psoriasis.  Extracts from the bark and root also act against, trypanosoma, the parasite that causes sleeping sickness and this confirms its use as a traditional treatment of sleeping sickness.The wood pulp is suitable for paper production and can also be used as firewood and for making charcoal.